# Matplotlib / Seaborn Standards

## SETUP

- MUST use:
  fig, ax = plt.subplots()

- MUST define figure size:
  figsize=(10, 6)

## STYLE

- USE seaborn theme:
  sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid" OR "ticks")

- REMOVE unnecessary spines:
  sns.despine()

## LABELING

- MUST include:
  - title
  - subtitle (via plt.text or ax.text)
  - x and y labels

## COLORS

- USE:
  sns.color_palette("colorblind")

## ANNOTATIONS

- USE ax.annotate() for key insights

## OUTPUT

- MUST call:
  plt.tight_layout()

## FORBIDDEN

- default matplotlib styling (unstyled charts)
- missing labels
- overlapping elements